Government drought measures under consideration include payments up to $100,000 to  drought-stricken farmers and easing 1989 crop acreage controls, but are called too slow.
Iowa farmers still face disaster despite five inches of weekend rain.
Barges with pumps  will haul fresh water to towns affected by the lower Mississippi River's rising salt levels.
A record expanse of US territory suffered drought in May and June.
In May, more  money was withdrawn from savings accounts than deposited for the first time in seven  months.
Stock prices, the dollar, and bond prices rose.
Grain, soybean, wheat, and oat  futures dropped.
Gold prices fell sharply. 
